content.description: The crux is getting to the first ledge of the climb. Starts out with some tough thin and crimpy moves. Very fun climb.
content.protection: Shares bolt anchors with "A Dream within a Dream". Use 2 longer slings on the anchors over the edge to save your rope. Toprope this problem.
content.location: Located just right of "A Dream within a Dream".

content.description: Short problem left of Dream within a dream. Couple of fun moves, harder for short people.
content.protection:
Pad or may be TR'ed from tree above.

Landing area kinda sketch, recomend TR

content.description: This is the route about 3 feet south of E Tu Brute, I am not sure of the name. it starts out with some tough crimpy moves and then gets real juggy at the top. I would give this 2 stars if it wasn't so short. When we climbed this it was raining pretty good and was slippery, so it could be easier than it seemed when dry.
content.protection: 2 bolts up top to set up anchor.

content.description: This route climbs the arete on the South side of the wall, a fun little short climb.

This is the beginning of the picturesque wall, lots of bouldering possibilities here, we didn't find it until late in the evening which killed our possibilities of getting ropes set up. I named the route damn smith and tusting because they published bad info on how to get the this wall. They did however point boulderers to a semi-sweet wall. That wall however is not the picturesque wall.
Just fun and good climbing here.
content.protection: 3 bolts and 2 anchors up top.  Use 2 longer slings on the anchors over the edge to save your rope.
content.location: Its the only bolted route on the wall.  Walk off the top.

content.description: This route is a good warmup for the front face of the wall.  Short climb but fun.
content.protection: Set up a top rope around the tree. 30 ft of webbing is needed.  There is no fixed gear for this route.
content.location: This route is uphill and to the right of Raven.  Small crimps.  Walk off the top.
